From: Vincent Fortier
Date: Fri, 30 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH] avcodec/hw_base_encode: fix DPB/ref overflow when pick_next
         is re-entered after an encode failure

When op->issue fails, the picture is never marked encode_issued, so
hw_base_encode_pick_next() is re-entered on the same picture on the next
call and re-runs the DPB / reference / prev setup at the end of the
function. hw_base_encode_add_ref() does not de-duplicate, so every
re-entry appends again and eventually trips an av_assert0():
  - nb_dpb_pics overflow (hw_base_encode.c:61) -- the originally reported
    case, with a closed-GOP IDR where only the self-DPB add runs;
  - for non-IDR pictures the setup also re-adds the forward reference, and
    hw_base_encode_add_ref(pic, ..., 0, 0, 1) then hits av_assert0(!pic->prev)
    because pic->prev is already set from the previous attempt (the L0/L1
    ref adds likewise grow nb_refs).

pick_next() always adds the picture to its own DPB first, so a non-zero
nb_dpb_pics means the setup already ran; in that case just return the
already-prepared picture instead of building it again.

Reproducible with h264_vaapi on Intel Apollo Lake after repeated
VA_STATUS_ERROR_ENCODING_ERROR (code 24) failures on a 1280x720@60fps
MPEG2 IPTV input stream.

Suggested-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>

--- libavcodec/hw_base_encode.c.orig
+++ libavcodec/hw_base_encode.c
@@ -325,6 +325,16 @@
     pic->is_reference = 1;
     *pic_out = pic;
 
+    /* If pic was already set up on a previous call, return it unchanged. After an
+     * encode failure (op->issue error) the picture is never marked encode_issued, so
+     * pick_next() is re-entered on it; re-running the DPB/reference/prev setup below
+     * would re-add entries -- hw_base_encode_add_ref() does not de-duplicate -- until
+     * an av_assert0() fires (nb_dpb_pics or nb_refs overflow, or the !pic->prev
+     * assert for non-IDR pictures). The self-DPB add always makes nb_dpb_pics >= 1, so
+     * a non-zero value means the setup already ran. */
+    if (pic->nb_dpb_pics)
+        return 0;
+
     hw_base_encode_add_ref(pic, pic, 0, 1, 0);
     if (pic->type != FF_HW_PICTURE_TYPE_IDR) {
         // TODO: apply both previous and forward multi reference for all vaapi encoders.
